JOHANNESBURG – The DA is confident it will reach an agreement over the appointment of Natasha Mazzone as second deputy federal chairperson. Senior DA member, Khume Ramulifho, lodged a complaint saying she has been appointed without an election being held. READ: 'Diverse' DA’s new leadership more of the same DA federal council chairperson James Selfe said: “There is one or two ways the one is to settle it I am certain that we will be able to persuade each other without going to court. The other way would be sort of the review application of the decision of the federal legal commission. The third way would be for us joint decide to jointly join the court on whether or not the federal legal commission made the right decision. But I am certain that we will be able to settle this amicably.” eNCA